<br>
I got MB a month ago and I've been playing around with it since then. I'm not uber at all. Yeah, MB showed me the truth about my mana pool size, and used to do between 6300 and 6800, (depending on having KEI or not, I guess) always in XP groups, and always being FM.<br>
<br>
I had yesterday the chance to use it for the first time in a raid situation against Severilous in EJ, and to my surprise, I hit for 8200. I expected a little more damage than usual because now I have Allegiant Familiar but, I just couldn't believe that the extra mana pool it gives were so big as to let me hit for that amount, so I went to crunch some numbers. Actually, not too much numbers to crunch. I found out that Allegiant Fam. just increases mana pool by 100 more than its predecesor, so, that would do 200 more dmg.<br>
<br>
The only different thing is that I was raid buffed instead of XP group buffed, and got my charm slot item for 3 flags.<br>
<br>
I don't know if there are any other buffs besides chanter's that can increase mana pools, and if they can stack.<br>
<br>
Any clue? Am I missing something? Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Hydralisk Hydralisk<br>
65 Sage Arcanist from Karana<br>
